Aminolysis of benzotriazolide 21 proceeded under mild conditions, especially in the presence of triethylamine (TEA). More than twenty ureas were prepared (22–37, 40, 53–58), including twin derivative 41, in which two PQ-moieties were linked with carbonyl group (Scheme 2
) [77,[79], [80], [81]]. Bis-derivative 41 was previously prepared by Kaur et al. [82]. The reaction of BtcPQ with O-benzylhydroxylamine gave compound 59, which afforded N-hydroxyurea 60 after catalytic hydrogenation [77]. Finally, compound 21 with hydrazine hydrate gave PQ-semicarbazide 61, a useful intermediate in the further reaction steps (Scheme 3
) [80].
